By CHIAZO OGBOLU LAGOS- The Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA) said that 20 ships at the Lagos Port Complex were discharging petrol and other items. The NPA disclosed this in its publication, ‘Shipping Position’, a copy of which was made available to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Wednesday in Lagos. It listed the items being discharged as bulk wheat, general cargo, container, bulk urea, bulk salt, bulk sugar, frozen fish, butane gas and petrol. The NPA said it was also expecting 10 other laden with frozen fish, containers, bulk sugar, bulk urea, base oil, bulk gypsum, soya bean meal and petrol from Jan. 11 to Jan. 16. It indicated that two other ships had arrived the port waiting to berth with container and petrol. (NAN)